Captain Siya Kolisi used the moment to call on South Africans to do what the players did and be united in their diversity. #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - Springbok captain Siya Kolisi is calling on all South Africans to do what the players did and be united in their diversity. The Rugby World Cup-winning Springboks are in Cape Town parading the World Cup trophy. READ: Tutu celebrates Springboks victory Kolisi said, "Look at how we are all different, different races, different backgrounds. We came together for South Africa and made it happen. Its time for us to stop fighting and stop arguing and put South Africa first." Cape Town is the final leg of the Bok's World Cup trophy tour. Watch the Bok captain speak in the video above.